Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.99,0:00:13.00,Default,,0,0,0,,We’re very happy for Daniel. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.74,0:00:18.00,Default,,0,0,0,,He’s going to be a blessing \Nin his new assignment. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.25,0:00:26.21,Default,,0,0,0,,But we are going to miss him \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.21,0:00:29.22,Default,,0,0,0,,and everything he was doing \Nfor the congregation. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.22,0:00:32.00,Default,,0,0,0,,This will change things for us.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:40.69,0:00:43.11,Default,,0,0,0,,We really want to be there \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:43.11,0:00:46.00,Default,,0,0,0,,for our brothers and sisters.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:13.93,0:01:15.93,Default,,0,0,0,,And it’s true: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:15.93,0:01:20.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Having plenty to do \Nin the Lord’s work is good. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:20.34,0:01:24.00,Default,,0,0,0,,But where will we get more help?\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:30.28,0:01:33.28,Default,,0,0,0,,We do have good ministerial servants \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:33.28,0:01:36.00,Default,,0,0,0,,like Richie. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:41.00,0:01:45.75,Default,,0,0,0,,But after Daniel left, \Nour elder body is one fewer now. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:45.75,0:01:48.50,Default,,0,0,0,,That prompted a good question: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:48.50,0:01:53.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Are we doing all we can \Nto train our brothers?\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.60,0:02:01.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Richie, do you have some time for me? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.95,0:02:04.02,Default,,0,0,0,,I have some calls you can help me with.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.02,0:02:07.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Sure, I’d like that.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.15,0:02:14.41,Default,,0,0,0,,I realized it had been \Na while since we talked \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.41,0:02:16.41,Default,,0,0,0,,about him qualifying to do more. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.41,0:02:19.24,Default,,0,0,0,,He explained that he wanted to help \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.24,0:02:21.29,Default,,0,0,0,,but didn’t want to appear presumptuous. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.29,0:02:23.29,Default,,0,0,0,,He’d been praying about it, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.29,0:02:27.13,Default,,0,0,0,,and he wanted to know what else \Nhe could do to keep reaching out.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.13,0:02:31.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Talking to Richie \Nmade me think of Jesus’ example. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.26,0:02:36.89,Default,,0,0,0,,His disciples offered themselves willingly, \Nand he trained them. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.89,0:02:39.97,Default,,0,0,0,,They were eager but needed his direction. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.97,0:02:43.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Jesus’ training gave them confidence \Nto do the assignments he gave them. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.90,0:02:49.23,Default,,0,0,0,,They were happy, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.23,0:02:51.23,Default,,0,0,0,,not just to follow Jesus, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.23,0:02:54.07,Default,,0,0,0,,but to work alongside him. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.07,0:02:57.70,Default,,0,0,0,,And Jesus was happy to share his work.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.70,0:03:00.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Up to his final evening with them, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.08,0:03:03.00,Default,,0,0,0,,he prepared them for the work ahead. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.00,0:03:05.12,Default,,0,0,0,,“Most truly I say to you, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.12,0:03:09.63,Default,,0,0,0,,“whoever exercises faith in me \Nwill also do the works that I do; \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.63,0:03:11.71,Default,,0,0,0,,“and he will do works greater than these, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.71,0:03:15.00,Default,,0,0,0,,because I am going my way to the Father.”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.63,0:03:22.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I now remember how much training \NI had received from the brothers.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.73,0:03:32.94,Default,,0,0,0,,It was easy to forget \Nthat I didn’t always get \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.94,0:03:36.00,Default,,0,0,0,,things right at first. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.93,0:03:46.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Soon, \NRichie was taking on more responsibility. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.71,0:03:51.00,Default,,0,0,0,,And he told me something \Nthat I too once felt. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.38,0:03:55.64,Default,,0,0,0,,He just didn’t realize how much work \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.64,0:03:58.00,Default,,0,0,0,,went into caring for Jehovah’s sheep. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.98,0:04:21.68,Default,,0,0,0,,But once he knew, \Nhe was glad he offered himself willingly.\N
